## 17. EFFETS VISUELS DYNAMIQUES

### A. Parallax Scroll Effect

```css
/* Container avec perspective */
.parallax-container {
  perspective: 1px;
  height: 100vh;
  overflow-x: hidden;
  overflow-y: auto;
}

/* √âl√©ment en parallax */
.parallax-layer {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  transform-style: preserve-3d;
}

.parallax-layer.background {
  transform: translateZ(-1px) scale(2);
  /* Bouge plus lentement que le scroll */
}

.parallax-layer.foreground {
  transform: translateZ(0);
  /* Bouge √† la vitesse normale */
}
```

**JavaScript pour parallax fluide :**

```javascript
window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
  const scrolled = window.pageYOffset;
  const parallaxElements = document.querySelectorAll('.parallax');
  
  parallaxElements.forEach(el => {
    const speed = el.dataset.speed || 0.5;
    el.style.transform = `translateY(${scrolled * speed}px)`;
  });
});
```

### B. Morphing Shapes (Animation fluide)

```css
@keyframes morph {
  0%, 100% {
    border-radius: 60% 40% 30% 70% / 60% 30% 70% 40%;
  }
  25% {
    border-radius: 30% 60% 70% 40% / 50% 60% 30% 60%;
  }
  50% {
    border-radius: 50% 60% 30% 60% / 30% 60% 70% 40%;
  }
  75% {
    border-radius: 60% 40% 60% 40% / 70% 50% 40% 50%;
  }
}

.organic-shape {
  width: 200px;
  height: 200px;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FF6B6B, #FFA07A);
  animation: morph 8s ease-in-out infinite;
  opacity: 0.1;
  position: absolute;
  filter: blur(40px);
}
```

### C. Animated Gradient Background

